description: For sale: $119,900. Welcome to your home-away-from home on the North Shore OR make it your primary residence! Newly remodeled 3-bedroom, 1 bath ranch home with full basement,nestled on the hill overlooking the City of Beaver Bay and Lake Superior! Wake up to gorgeous sunrises or unwind in the evening, watching the Lakers with the views!Home has been extensively remodeled with new vinyl siding, windows and roof; paint throughout, laminate wood flooring on main floor, new bathroom fixtures, new Thomasville kitchen cabinets with self-closing drawers and counter tops, new sump crock and laundry tub. This home is completely ready for you to unlock the door and make it your home! Property is minutes to the Red Dot Trail for snowmobiling or four-wheeling and to the Gitchi-Gami State Trail for hiking, biking, rollerblading. Walk to the playground, restaurants and shopping, fishing and hiking along the Beaver River and the public beach of Lake Superior. Four seasons of fun and nature awaits! The Silver Bay Safe Harbor Public Marina boat launch offers you lake access, Black Beach, North Shore Adventure Park, Silver Bay shopping center for all your shopping needs, and St. Luke's Bay Area Medical Clinic are all just minutes north of this home. Located 1 hour north of Duluth, 2 ½ hours south of the Canadian Border. Call today for your immediate showing!

description: For sale: $339,900. Wonderful Lake Superior Townhome with spectacular view from every room in the house.  This beautiful, well kept home is currently being lived in year round.  It is a spacious 2 Bedroom 2 bathroom with loft area that is currently being used as an office.  Stunning 20' ceiling to enhance the natural light form all levels, and when that sun is too bright you can use the motorized blinds to control your amount of sunlight.  The Master Suite has wonderful views and lots of space for dressers, workout equipment or comfy chairs to watch the boats go by.  Many updates for these owners are the engineered hardwoods in the Kitchen, living room, and dining room area, appliances, complete vapor barrier in the basement and a new furnace and water heater.  This Townhome is on the south end of the building so you do get a lot of natural lighting which is wonderful, and is connected to City sewer and water.  Another bonus for owning in this development is you have access to the pool and sauna, plowing, lawn care, exterior maintenance and garbage all included in your monthly HOA fee. * We are not accepting showings at this time.

description: For sale: $389,000. This Cottage is nestled in the woods with a view of Lake Superior.  The Cove at Cove Point Lodge is a hidden treasure with a walking path to the point, kayak or Canoe launch and a swimming beach. Private and comfortable with a sense of isolation this cabin offers you the best of the North Shore. Cove Point Lodge is the center of North Shore activity, close to Superior Hiking Trail, the Gitchi-Gami Bike Trail, Split Rock Lighthouse State park, ski trails and so much more.   The cottage is sold furnished and ready for your use.   It is optional to join the Cove Point Lodge rental program that can offer a revenue return to offset your cottage expenses.  Call today for a showing or for more information on Ownership.
